<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-06T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="562" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">381.81/327: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Acting American Representative to the French
                                    Committee of National Liberation</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-06T17:00:00+02:00">April
                                        6, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 7—9:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1139. Your 926, March 28, 2 p.m. American military authorities here
                                state that they have made exhaustive investigation and have failed
                                to discover any indications whatsoever that an agreement such as
                                that mentioned in first paragraph of Russell’s telegram 76, March
                                24, 5 p.m. was entered into between American and French authorities
                                in Algiers. At their request we phoned Russell and asked for further
                                particulars which he said he would immediately endeavor to obtain
                                for transmission here.</p>
                            <p>Will telegraph further developments.</p>
                            <p>Your 926, March 28, 2 p.m. was repeated to Tangier, Casablanca and
                                Rabat.</p>
                            <p>Sent to the Department as 1139; repeated to Tangier as 25; repeated
                                to Rabat as 5; repeated to Casablanca as 6.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>